  "definition": {
    "en": "Freeze-dried BCG Vaccine (for Percutaneous Use) is a preparation for injection which is dissolved before use. It contains live bacteria derived from a culture of the bacillus of Calmette and Gueárin."
  },
  "appearance": {
    "en": "Freeze-dried BCG Vaccine (for Percutaneous Use) becomes a white to light yellow, turbid liquid on addi-tion of solvent. Beclometasone Dipropionate"
  }
}